Reasoning: The paper discusses a categorical model of computation and provides a coalgebraic characterization of it. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Computer Science (cs.CS), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on category theory and coalgebraic methods, cs.LO and cs.PL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the graphical language of string diagrams, which could potentially place it in cs.CC or cs.DS.
